<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>The Faculty AI Navigator</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
    <style>
        .section-card { @apply bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-100 mb-8; }
        .executive-summary { @apply italic text-gray-600 border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4 mb-4; }
    </style>
</head>
<body class="bg-gray-50 text-gray-800 leading-relaxed">

    <header class="bg-slate-900 text-white py-12 px-6 shadow-md text-center">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-2">The Faculty AI Navigator</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-slate-300">A Centralized Hub for AI in Teaching and Research</p>
    </header>

    <main class="max-w-5xl mx-auto py-10 px-6">
        
        <section class="mb-12 text-center">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Empowering Faculty with Ethical AI Integration</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto">This resource library is designed to help university educators understand, navigate, and implement Artificial Intelligence with academic rigor and integrity.</p>
        </section>

        <div class="section-card">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-700 mb-4">I. AI Literacy 101</h2>
            <p class="executive-summary">Understanding Large Language Models (LLMs) is a foundational digital literacy. This section demystifies how AI predicts patterns helping faculty set realistic expectations.</p>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                <div>
                    <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Key Takeaways</h3>
                    <ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1">
                        <li>LLMs function on probability, not facts.</li>
                        <li>Prompting follows: Context, Task, and Constraint.</li>
                        <li>Understand Multimodal (text, image, data) tools.</li>
                        <li>AI requires human oversight for substance.</li>
                        <li>Tool-specific leaders (ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini).</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-blue-50 p-4 rounded">
                    <h3 class="font-bold text-blue-800 mb-2">💡 Quick Start Tip</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm">Treat the AI like a highly capable but literal-minded teaching assistant; give it a specific persona and clear instructions.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section-card">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-700 mb-4">II. Syllabus & Policy Templates</h2>
            <p class="executive-summary">Clear communication is the best defense. We provide tiered language options to align AI policies with specific learning objectives.</p>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                <div>
                    <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Action Items</h3>
                    <ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1">
                        <li>Level 1 (Red): Strict "No AI" policy.</li>
                        <li>Level 2 (Yellow): "Assisted Use" for brainstorming.</li>
                        <li>Level 3 (Green): "Full Integration" for AI literacy.</li>
                        <li>Include an "AI Disclosure Statement" requirement.</li>
                        <li>Discuss the *why* behind your policy with students.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-blue-50 p-4 rounded">
                    <h3 class="font-bold text-blue-800 mb-2">💡 Quick Start Tip</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm">Add a "Traffic Light" icon to each assignment description so students know the AI status at a glance.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section-card">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-700 mb-4">III. Pedagogical Strategies</h2>
            <p class="executive-summary">Shift from "product-based" to "process-based" evaluation. Redesign assignments to leverage or minimize AI influence effectively.</p>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                <div>
                    <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Key Strategies</h3>
                    <ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1">
                        <li>AI-Resistant: Use in-class reflections and local prompts.</li>
                        <li>AI-Integrated: Have students critique AI drafts.</li>
                        <li>Focus on personal voice and lived experience.</li>
                        <li>Scaffolded assignments (Grade drafts separately).</li>
                        <li>Use AI for "Socratic Tutoring" sessions.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-blue-50 p-4 rounded">
                    <h3 class="font-bold text-blue-800 mb-2">💡 Quick Start Tip</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm">Ask students to submit their "AI Chat Log" along with their paper to see their reasoning process.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <footer class="text-center py-10 text-gray-500 text-sm">
            <p>&copy; 2026 The Faculty AI Navigator. Built for Academic Excellence.</p>
        </footer>

    </main>
</body>
</html>
